    "causal_summary": "Three defensive front-proxy fixes so an externally-killed or slow-booting mk-spec-memory daemon never presents as an indefinite 'connecting…' hang: bound the proxy cold-start probe window (120->30 attempts, ~176s->~41s, env-tunable), fail-fast with a retryable -32001 JSON-RPC error on an unbridgeable lease-held secondary session, and make the daemon lazy-init FATALs throw (caller gets a structured tool error + the init guard retries) instead of process.exit downing the shared daemon for every client.",
